\b \cf2 Requirements:
\b0 \
Working internet connection\
\

\b How to Generate a SSDT for Power Management
\b0 \
\
1. Configure system with appropriate SMBIOS for your CPU using Clover Configurator\
\
2. Open Terminal and download Piker Alpha's ssdtPRGen.sh\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf2 \cb5 Code (Text):\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 curl -o ~/ssdtPRGen.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Piker-Alpha/ssdtPRGen.sh/master/ssdtPRGen.sh\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 3. That will download ssdtPRGen.sh to your user directory. The next step is to change the file mode (+x) with:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf2 \cb5 Code (Text):\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 chmod +x ~/ssdtPRGen.sh\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 4. For default SSDT generation, type:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf2 \cb5 Code (Text):\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 sudo ~/ssdtPRGen.sh\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 5. Type n, n\
\
6. Open Finder and in menubar choose Go/Go to Folder...\
\
7. Type ~/Library/ssdtPRGen/\
\
8. Mount EFI using {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.tonymacx86.com/downloads.php?do=cat&id=10"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 EFI Mounter v3}}\
\
9. Copy SSDT.aml to /Volumes/EFI/EFI/CLOVER/ACPI/patched/\
\
NOTE: The Power Management SSDT should always be SSDT.aml. If you have an SSDT.aml there already, rename it SSDT-1.aml, etc...\
\
10. Reboot\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\partightenfactor0

